Sentence: She only ate the apple.
She : pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "ate"
only : restrictive adverb, focuses negation on "the apple" indicating exclusivity
ate : verb "eat", past tense, third person singular, active voice
the : definite article, singular
apple : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "ate"

Sentence: He barely finished the report.
He : pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "finished"
barely : restrictive adverb, focuses negation on "finished" indicating it almost did not happen
finished : verb "finish", past tense, third person singular, active voice
the : definite article, singular
report : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "finished"

Sentence: They hardly knew the answer.
They : pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb "knew"
