Sentence: She hardly ever visits her grandmother.
She : pronoun, third person singular, subject of the verb "visits"
hardly : restrictive adverb, part of the phrase "hardly ever" focusing negation on frequency
ever : adverb, intensifies "hardly" to mean almost never
visits : verb "visit", present tense, third person singular, active voice
